86.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> Im new to the mage class (level 24) and I am wondering at every spell level should I research all the pets I need to? Or just go with the one or two we can buy?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks for the time <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nucci01>Nucci 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 1:09:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> Just go with the 1 or 2 you can buy til 39 or 44(unless all you get it fire), because the levels below that come so fast it won't make much difference. At level 44 you can buy all 4 pets in Katta and then you will want all 4 49 pets which you will have sufficient time to research and after 49 there is no more research(yay!!!).<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 1:51:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> My gut feeling is yes, do the research, but you asked a loaded question.  What pets have you used thus far?  Have you used them all enough to know how they work for you in combat?  Do you have a strong preference/dislike for a pet or pets? The rotation of purchaseable pets tends to be earth and air or fire and water. If you depend heavily on one pet or don't like the two that purchaseable at a level, you're in trouble if you don't research.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 648<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 9:55:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> From around level 29 on, I would typically have a single hunting spot per 'spell circle', so it wasn't necessary to research all of the pet spells.<br>
<br>
Your style of play and choice of hunting grounds will determine which pets you will need to have around.<br>
<br>
In the mid levels (24-39) the fire pet is actually pretty strong with its innate DS, I found it fairly efficient for soloing.<br>
<br>
If you tend to do more grouping, you will want other choices...... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 56th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lehtotinkertank>LehtoTinkertank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(12/13/02 4:36:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> I am new to the Mage scene. My toon is only level 17 atm. All my other chars have been melee types so casting and research are new to me . Please exscuse the nOOb question.<br>
<br>
Is there a preffered spot to get the words needed to research. (vendor or mob)?<br>
<br>
Where can i find a list of the spells that can be researched?<br>
<br>
Is it only pet spells that need researching? (I have seen the nulify magic spell can be researched but am told that its not worth it cause I wont really use it)<br>
<br>
Is there a place that I can buy the level 16 pets? (being a DEF with only evil faction atm)<br>
Any help would be appreciated. Thank You<br>
<br>
Ocularis Infernum<br>
<br>
Karana Server<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=archangelranari@themagicianstower>Archangel Ranari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#333333>(12/13/02 4:39:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> Or, you can bypass the research bullcrap and develope skills with the vendor bought pets.  I'm personally an air pet fan, but I made the time to learn the strengths and weaknesses of each individual pet simply by forcing myself to use them.<br>
<br>
You might want to check the bazaar too.  Sometimes, you'll get one of the old school mages who researched a bunch of lower level pet spells and sells them pretty cheap.  <br>
<br>
Also, DO THE FOCUS ITEM QUESTS!!!   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 651<br> <font color=#333333>(12/13/02 5:04:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=886.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pets? research?</span><hr size=1> The best place to find components is on vendors near the zones in which they drop. This is made much easier present day due to the 80 slot NPC's. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Some places to look (you'll need to modify to suit your own faction):<br>
<br>
Windmill in LOIO<br>
Gypsy Camp in NK<br>
Gypsy Camp &amp; Druid Ring in Lavastorm<br>
Jaggedpine Vendors<br>
Bazaar<br>
PoK<br>
<br>
As a general rule, the mobs that drop the words/items for the spells you will currently need to research will not be solo'able. So either bring a group, or hit the vendors hard...... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
